Joseph SACHS, doing business as Atlantic Liquor Wholesalers, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. BROWN-FORMAN DISTILLERS CORPORATION, Defendant-Appellee. No. 358, Docket 23936. United States Court of Appeals Second Circuit. Argued May 17, 18, 1956. Decided June 29, 1956. Krause, Hirseh, Levin & Heilpern, New York City (Sydney Krause and Charles Singer, New York City, of counsel), for plaintiff-appellant. White & Case, New York City (Thomas Kiernan and Ernest A. Fintel, New York City, of counsel), for defendant-appellee.

Before MEDINA, LUMBARD and WATERMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Affirmed on the opinion of Judge Wein-feld, reported at 134 F.Supp. 9.
